						<summary>

						<p>On two fragments of a slab lying near the Gangamma temple.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya (Rudra)dēva: 1268 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1190, [Pra]bhava, Phālguṇa śu. 15, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to 1268 A.D., February 29, f.d.t. 74.</p>						

						<p>It records the grant of income <hi rend="italic">(suvarnādāyam)</hi> made for the worship of god probably Siddhanāthadēva at Jyōti by a subordinate (name lost) of the king, who bears some epithets like <hi rend="italic">māṇḍalikabrahmarākshasa</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Jagaddaḷa Gaṇḍapeṇḍāra.</hi> The epigraph was written by a certain individual <hi rend="italic">karaṇam</hi> kavi.</p>						

						</summary>
